    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>When you create an array of size 10 it allocated 10 slots but from 0 to 9.\nThis for loop might help you see that a little better.</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Array {\n    int[] data = new int[10]; \n    /** Creates a new instance of an int Array */\n    public Array() {\n        for(int i = 0; i &lt; data.length; i++) {\n            data[i] = i*10;\n        }\n    }\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
