    "body" : "<p><strong>Rather than learning un-Official websites learn from oracle website</strong></p>\n\n<p>link follows:<a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/arrays.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Click here</a></p>\n\n<p><strong>*You can find Initialization as well as declaration with full description *</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>int n; // size of array here 10\nint[] a = new int[n];\nfor (int i = 0; i &lt; a.length; i++)\n{\n    a[i] = Integer.parseInt(s.nextLine()); // using Scanner class\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>Input</strong>:\n10//array size\n10\n20\n30\n40\n50\n60\n71\n80\n90\n91</p>\n\n<p><strong>Displaying data:</strong></p>\n\n<pre><code>for (int i = 0; i &lt; a.length; i++) \n{\n    System.out.println(a[i] + \" \");\n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p><strong>Output:</strong>\n10 20 30 40 50 60 71 80 90 91</p>\n"
  }, {
