  "title" : "How to initialize an array in Java?",
  "body" : "<p>I am initializing an array like this:</p>\n\n<pre><code>public class Array {\n\n    int data[] = new int[10]; \n    /** Creates a new instance of Array */\n    public Array() {\n        data[10] = {10,20,30,40,50,60,71,80,90,91};\n    }     \n}\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>NetBeans points to an error at this line: </p>\n\n<pre><code>data[10] = {10,20,30,40,50,60,71,80,90,91};\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>How can I solve the problem?</p>\n"
}